WEBVTT

00:08.708 --> 00:10.583
Five eleven is your change.

00:10.583 --> 00:13.125
Um, did you look at
the bill I gave you?

00:13.125 --> 00:16.250
Uh, yes, I gave you
change for two 20s.

00:16.250 --> 00:19.125
I know,
but take a good look at it,

00:19.125 --> 00:20.958
'cause I wrote my
phone number on it.

00:23.500 --> 00:26.000
Intentionally marking currency
is a federal offense.

00:27.333 --> 00:29.291
Look, it was just
my silly way

00:29.291 --> 00:31.125
of seeing if you'd like
to go out some time.

00:31.125 --> 00:32.375
My name's Sara.

00:37.250 --> 00:40.500
Look, uh...
Sara, I'm sorry.

00:40.500 --> 00:43.000
It's just that you remind me
of my old girlfriend.

00:43.750 --> 00:45.625
She was a girl, too.

00:47.583 --> 00:50.000
Looks like I got a lot
in common with her.

00:50.000 --> 00:52.000
Because I'm also a girl...

00:52.000 --> 00:53.583
...who thinks you're cute.

00:53.583 --> 00:55.000
Oh, great.

00:55.000 --> 00:57.750
Now you're exactly like her.
She thought I was cute, too.

00:59.291 --> 01:01.250
What else? Do you
like my clammy hands?

01:01.250 --> 01:03.875
She loved my clammy hands.
Go ahead, feel my clammy hands!

01:03.875 --> 01:06.625
Wow! That was
a little dramatic.

01:06.625 --> 01:10.250
Good thing your next
girlfriend likes drama.

01:12.416 --> 01:14.458
Call me.

01:16.000 --> 01:17.833
we used to do that, too!

01:22.208 --> 01:24.500
Oh my gosh, that cute girl
was totally into you.

01:24.500 --> 01:26.000
How could you just
blow her off like that?

01:26.000 --> 01:28.166
Because an appropriate amount
of time has not passed

01:28.166 --> 01:29.958
since I lost Juliet.

01:29.958 --> 01:32.083
And that appropriate amount
of time will be in the year...

01:32.083 --> 01:34.333
...two thousand and never!

01:37.083 --> 01:39.333
Justin, I know you're
hurting from losing Juliet,

01:39.333 --> 01:40.875
but you've got to find
a way to move on.

01:40.875 --> 01:45.166
Son, I remember
when John Bender,

01:45.166 --> 01:47.125
Benjamin Kenobi, Ponyboy, and I

01:47.125 --> 01:48.875
were all in love
with the same girl.

01:48.875 --> 01:51.458
Mary-Ann Delou.

01:51.458 --> 01:52.875
And I had to just
face the fact

01:52.875 --> 01:54.750
that they had cool names
and I didn't.

01:54.750 --> 01:57.000
And it was... Oh, I know
what you're thinking.

01:57.000 --> 01:58.750
You're thinking this story
has nothing to do

01:58.750 --> 02:00.958
with your situation.
And you're probably right.

02:02.083 --> 02:03.958
But I got stuff going on too,

02:03.958 --> 02:06.458
and sometimes I need
to talk about it.

02:13.958 --> 02:16.375
There were so many things I
wanted to do with Juliet.

02:16.375 --> 02:19.250
Like... Like see
the Grand Canyon,

02:19.250 --> 02:21.083
or swim with dolphins.

02:21.083 --> 02:24.875
I didn't even get to
take her on a boat ride in
Central Park for her birthday.

02:24.875 --> 02:28.250
Oh, look, dude, the chick got
scratched by a werewolf, OK?

02:28.250 --> 02:31.625
She turned old,
like, 2,193 years old,

02:31.625 --> 02:35.000
and then dragged her wrinkly
self into the woods forever.

02:35.000 --> 02:36.416
Let her go.

02:37.500 --> 02:41.458
OK, first of all,
it's 2,194 tomorrow.

02:41.458 --> 02:43.500
Maybe that's why I'm so upset!

02:43.500 --> 02:46.583
Maybe that's why I could use
a little sympathy from you guys.

02:49.708 --> 02:51.708
Alex, take it easy on him.

02:51.708 --> 02:54.833
Look, sometimes you just gotta
yank the bandage right off.

02:54.833 --> 02:56.250
That's what I did
with Mason.

02:56.250 --> 02:59.875
It was hard, but I'm ready
for my next relationship now.

02:59.875 --> 03:02.958
And I know when it happens,
we're gonna be together forever.

